SEC. 4. The Institute shall have the following specific powers and functions:

develop productive, high yielding, good quality and pest/disease resistant varieties/strains of mulberry and silkworm;

produce adequate certified mulberry planting materials and high quality silkworm eggs;

develop efficient, economic and productive mulberry leaf production, preservation and utilization technologies;

develop sound and productive silkworm rearing technology;

develop the production and fabrication of reeling and re-reeling machineries suitable for rural use;

develop effective mulberry and silkworm pests management strategies;

evolve productive farming systems compatible with mulberry leaf production;

develop efficient and effective local and international marketing systems;

develop and implement appropriate and applicable technology packages and effective technology dissemination and utilization systems, particularly the conduct of training programs;

upgrade skills of farmers and their families, development agents and extension workers through trainings, seminars and workshops on mulberry leaf production and storage, silkworm rearing for industrial and seed cocoon production, reeling and re-reeling, handloom weaving and other silk product and by-product utilization;

coordinate with the Don Mariano Marcos Memorial State University in the conduct of higher and advanced sericulture degree programs;

coordinate with other government/private agencies involved in the development of sericulture as a rural-based industry in the country.

SEC. 6. The plans and programs of the Institute shall be reviewed annually by an Advisory Board composed of:

the Secretary of Agriculture, as Chairman;

the University President of the Don Mariano Marcos Memorial State University, as Vice Chairman;

the Secretary of Trade and Industry, as Member;

the Executive Director of the Philippine Council for Agriculture, Forestry and Natural Resources Research and Development (PCARRD), as Member;

the Administrator of the Fiber Industry and Development Authority (FIDA), as Member;

the Director, Philippine Textile Research Institute (PTRI), as Member;

the Director, Sericulture Research and Development Institute (SRDI), as Member and Secretary;

one (1) representative from private associations or cooperatives or producers of mulberry and silk cocoon, as Member; and

one (1) representative from the local silk cloth processing and manufacturing industry, as Member.

SEC. 7. The presence of five (5) members at the time of the meeting shall constitute a

quorum: Provided, however,

That the Chairman or, in his absence, the Vice Chairman shall preside.
